  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to simply use `:uppercase?` prop for `[text]` component, so it should be \r\n\r\n`[text {:uppercase? true} \"Text\"]` - for Android\r\n\r\n`[text {:force-uppercase? true} \"Text\"]` - for both ios and Android\r\n\r\n```clojure\r\n(defn text\r\n  ([t]\r\n   (reagent/as-element [text-class t]))\r\n  ([{:keys [uppercase? force-uppercase?] :as opts} t & ts]\r\n   (reagent/as-element\r\n     (let [ts (cond->> (conj ts t)\r\n                       (or :force-uppercase? (and uppercase? platform/android?)) (map #(when % (string/upper-case %))))]\r\n       (vec (concat\r\n              [text-class (add-font-style :style opts)]\r\n              ts))))))\r\n```\r\n",
